# JARVIS voice policy (JONBEATZ.DEV)

OmniVoice is shared from the Hermes core install (`D:\Hermes\apps\OmniVoice` +
`_core-scripts\voice-engine`). It works here exactly like the personal profile —
ritual-only, never chatty.

## Default voices

| Priority | Engine | When |
|----------|--------|------|
| **Primary** | **OmniVoice** (British male, CPU) | Every allowed speak |
| **Backup** | Edge `en-GB-RyanNeural` | Only if OmniVoice fails |

## When to speak (allowed)

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| **Start Project** ritual | `npm run jarvis:speak -- "..."` once (greeting) |
| **End Project** ritual | `npm run jarvis:speak -- "..."` once (short farewell) |
| Jon says **speak**, **say**, **talk this**, **read aloud** | `npm run jarvis:speak -- "<exact text>"` |
| Critical **Mem0 / build / deploy errors** | Only if `JARVIS_VOICE_ERRORS=1` (default on) |

## When NOT to speak

- **Never** read ordinary chat replies or summaries aloud.
- **Never** speak after `mem0:add`, `mem0:search`, or successful Mem0 recall.
- **Never** start the OmniVoice daemon at PC boot — lazy start on first ritual speak;
  `npm run session:stop` stops it to free RAM.

## Commands

```powershell
npm run jarvis:speak -- "text"        # OmniVoice (Ryan fallback on failure)
npm run jarvis:voice-test             # one-line smoke test
npm run jarvis:omni-daemon            # optional pre-warm before Start Project
npm run jarvis:omni-daemon -- -Stop   # free RAM (also runs on session:stop)
```

Optional `.env.local` overrides: `JARVIS_VOICE_POLICY` (`ritual`/`off`),
`JARVIS_VOICE_ERRORS` (`1`/`0`), `OMNIVOICE_PYTHON`, `JARVIS_OMNI_PORT`.
